- Response schemas saved for UI integration

### 3. Complete UI Built ✓
- **Main Application**: `/app/nextjs-project/app/page.tsx`
- Two-column layout (40% upload/chat, 60% results)
- PDF upload with drag-and-drop
- Conversation interface with Discovery Coordinator
- 5-stage pipeline visualization
- Progressive disclosure of results
- Summary cards with expandable sections
- 5 related paper recommendations
- Quality assessment dashboard
- Export functionality
- Deep indigo (#4338CA) color scheme

---

## Key Features Implemented

### Upload & Input
- PDF drag-and-drop (up to 50MB)
- DOI input field
- arXiv URL input field
- Format validation

### Conversational Discovery
- Chat interface with Discovery Coordinator
- User prompt input for focus areas
- Message history
- Typing indicators

### Analysis Pipeline
- Visual 5-stage pipeline: Parsing → Understanding → Summarizing → Finding Papers → Quality Check
- Real-time progress indicators
- Progressive result loading

### Results Display
- Document information card
- Expandable summary sections:
  - Problem Statement
  - Methodology (with section citations)
  - Key Results
  - Limitations
- Key Takeaways with numbered highlights
- 5 Related Papers with:
  - Relevance scores
  - Authors, year, source
  - Relevance explanations
  - External links

### Additional Features
- Collapsible sidebar for research interests
- Quality assessment scores
- Export summary functionality
- Responsive design
- Error handling

---

## Integration Notes

- All AI interactions use `/app/nextjs-project/lib/aiAgent.ts`
- No toast/sonner notifications (as requested)
- No OAuth flows (handled by agents)
- Only react-icons used (no emojis)
- TypeScript interfaces built from actual test responses

